Dupuis 1913 : 83 (type locality: Taiwan [Moozan, Sokutsu]; syntypes in IRSN);
Jedlicka 1963
: 379; Kabak 2003 : 437 (catalogue).

Medium size species, body length 9.5-10.5 mm; dorsal surface black, elytra usually with faint cyan hue; anterior patch transverse, a little zigzag (more transverse and zigzag than 
P. o. ornatus
), usually in the fourth to sixth intervals; posterior patch separate, composed of three small spots, in intervals 2-3, 4-5, and 7 respectively. Pronotum transverse, PW/PL 1.50-1.58; lateral margins sinuate before posterior angles, posterior angles nearly rectangular; disc with fine wrinkles. Elytra flat; apical truncation distinctly curved; outer apical angles usually obtuse (Fig. 25), occasionally rounded (Fig. 26) or acute; sutural angles blunt; third interval usually with two setigerous pores (occasionally three as other species), the middle one usually missing. Median lobe of aedeagus with apical orifice opened to left-dorsal side (Fig. 39).
